---+!! Thursday  Exercise 2.0: HTCondor data transfer
%TOC%

---++ Goal

   * Often times, you&#39;ll need to transfer input files along with your HTCondor jobs.  Recall that OSG does not have a shared filesystem!   
   * In this tutorial we will learn how to specify input files to HTCondor and have HTCondor transfer files for each job.  The example itself is a molecular dynamics simulation of the Ubiquitin protein using the NAMD application.  

---++ Setup

Before we can start, we&#39;ll need to get the files used in this tutorial:

&lt;pre class=&quot;screen&quot;&gt;
%UCL_PROMPT_SHORT% &lt;strong&gt;cp -a /stash/public/userschool2015/namd ~ &lt;/strong&gt;
%UCL_PROMPT_SHORT% &lt;strong&gt;cd namd &lt;/strong&gt;
%UCL_PROMPT_SHORT% &lt;strong&gt;ls  &lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;file&quot;&gt;
namd-ct-local   #  Transfer input files from submit node to worker node
namd-ct-web    # Transfer input files from AWS server to worker node
namd-ct-stash  # Transfer input files from stash-public at submit node to worker node
&lt;/pre&gt;

